parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Rusted Brake Lines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rusted brake lines can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to ABS System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
vibration in the brake pedal or steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Warped Brake Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration and pulsation in the brake pedal, leading to a loss of braking power and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Vibration in the brake pedal or steering wheel
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering shimmy/vibration can cause loss of control, accidents, and unsafe driving conditions, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates
often between 50-65 mph
making it difficult to control the vehicle. The vibration can be felt in the steering wheel
and in some cases
the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inconsistent steering response can cause loss of control, accidents, and unsafe driving conditions, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle may drift to one side or require constant adjustments to stay in the center of the road
making it difficult to maintain control. The steering may feel weak or unpredictable
and the vehicle may respond differently to changes in road surface or weather conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pulsation can cause loss of control, accidents, and unsafe driving conditions, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The brakes may pulse or vibrate when slowing down
especially at high speeds
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seat belt retraction failure can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt may not retract properly
hanging up after a few inches
which can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the vehicle's safety and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Large holes in the frame
rust on metal and welds
corroded gas tank straps and fuel lines
broken gas tank straps
and significant safety concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The hood latch releases unexpectedly
the hood bounces up and down
and the safety catch fails to prevent the hood from opening.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature cracking of the windshield can impair the driver's vision, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Unreasonable and premature cracking of the windshield
even with minor impacts
such as pebbles hitting the windshield.
